In Antwerpen 17 febre1
Brussel Jan val
Mons. in antwoort vanden ul van 12 deser vinde mijne calaut tot
deboter geensins geinclineert soo hope die costij sult verkoopen als mede die
noch onderwegen leyt al soo daer weing kan met uijttreght vande
beesfactse sijn 50 veatten verkoght ge weestal hier & dan gesonden
aen de wed. Jan b vanderhagen tot brussel de welke soo ick verstaen
soude doen aftheuren voor over jaerschi & gevn belfaetse boter
soo wenste de goetheijt die eens te sien & te verstaen wat haere
pretentie is want ul de sleghte sort verkoopende a so14 ten minste
de dese is soo veel weirdigh, tis mij aengenaemdat ul voor mijn baye
devoir sal doen als voor eijgen in eenigh diergelijk decosie hebb liebertijt
te commandeeren
In Antwerpen 17 febr
Brugge Raphael Coots
mijnh nae afgaen van mijne van heden becomen abradare
van gisteren dels mij wegens het versoegh gerust stelt het begint voor
goet te dogen, & soo en twijffele niet of de vaert van oftedd voort
de lakens
t
gehoopt & hatt pack No. 86 gelieft ul onderde ƒ90 aen tegeven & het
beste te doen deselve met dobbelaer beneffens de soft packen te senden
als mede t8 N 21 a 23„ ick hope doo ul directie dat ulle engelsche spaense
lakens onder ƒ90 sullen passeren & dese clauselen die oock in devoright
lefte gementioneert waren geconsideert sullen worden alsvoren
het packie canten AI.SN.2 volght p desen vant voorders passerende
verneme geirne ul advies ul trato wert prompt voldaen en
verneme geirne hoe het met het gevoyer pack sal af loopen
om ter eguleeren voor ons tegen aen staende
In Antwarp 1
London Richd Southell
th
S. my last to you was on the 11: curitt sence recd recd. yd of 4 ditto
whore by perceave, that non of my formars wire come to handes
yett hope before this that you recd. them all stake noticd you shipt
he pack of fine cloth for auracct. in comp. for dunkerque, god
send then well over as also, good succes to all yd undertakeings
you brough a pack of gray dosins from im. adward Hill, selve
you are att the please I hope you will make a good bargin other
vise the factors somes times do not srruple to make a false
anvoyce & over rate that so much as they would faime yett
whaever I hope better seeng you approove of them to be penniwortts
what eder you do you must for be aredrawing on mee, for
noth withstand ing of £300 IHC drew pr last, yett an over charged
so that you must gett drawne up on yd trdd self for I do not
know how I shall boe able to gett oyer the stijle of next month
when the bills dew on you then wee can make a shist for
a longer rim & H.M. gives good creditt as to you propositions. wee
will easely aggred in case yd trade be driven att lille uponyd
namd towards caster wee may mee to as to the serges of mr. wood thy
are not att all propper for mee therefore I will not have them by n
meanes I long to have yd answer on my formar letters & so re
London Lucy kinghtley
Antwarp 18 feb 1681
th
S my ast to you was on the 15: curitt with a remise for £70 st on m.
Pieter do cochre Junior att 2 uso which I hope is safe come to yd handes
then also desired you to buy s0 duble dhedds for mee, butt sence have
yd of 30h past, where by perceave you have secured 10 reds of £92
10 of £10 s apr. & proffer the same to mee I do accept of y. & desire
you please to pack 5 of £425 of £10 in one bale as mucth
in am other bechouse they should be assorted when. I have occasion
to open them here, could desire you besides to buy Lauroras of £11:10
a £12: ap & putt them none of the bales, which will then cont
12 cloothes & the other 10 & ship them off a sunder, as you shall iudge
best: my other freindes of London content them selves now
with 3. for goods from thence & 4. from the north both
for provision & in surance, which I exspect will be also to yd content
for what hence forward I might desire from you as soone shave
yd advise shall in order some thingh more from costiy &p nont
remitt you att ssorter sight towards payement of saidred. N10
with kinde saluts
as yett nonews of John nelson yd bale
of kersies are come to handes that sort wee never hadhere, besides
tis pettij they did not comened monthes soones for I donbt with the
sommer they will not sell in case you beequally concerned in
the above saidred cloathes I leave to yd pleasure
London Will Stayten
In Antw: 18 feb 1681
th
S my last to you was on the 11: curitt to which referre you sence recd. yd
of 4: ditto inclosed a memoriall of the cast india sale ordered to be
on the 8:h marck, next Ill peruse itt & advise you p first what
wel shall most want I am informed, that you make itt yd butsyn
to sell laces, I shall send you one packett to dispose of for my acctt as
best you can for ready mony, onely to see how you finde goods
which I dayly provide, & for us how they render in England, that in case
you finde in corridgment, for I have a great delight there in
& buy dayly good quantities where fore itt must be kept priuate
that wee should be concerned in any thick of that nature, for what
I buy here for others is in comission so I exspect you to be my freind
there in Juse to send the packetts by may of Dover to mr. Eeaton, which
the forwards the same to london where fore in case you have any
other & securer con veniency pray lett mee know itt pr. first, as also
yd opinion att large & if any new assortement most demanded
thought I am confident that you nwer had such goods aso ordere
as you will see from my handes: so faile not to give mee yd answer
withbut delay, as also about the tykes if you please to have my
all what I have by mee, because a great deale of them is alread
bespoaken & ordered for London & so wish you all prospeirtie &
with kinde saluts remane
